Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
report_obj_connectivity(25.10)                  report_obj_connectivity(25.10)

Name
       report_obj_connectivity  - Reports the connections of specified macros,
       selected macros, or specified ports

Syntax
       report_obj_connectivity

       [-help]

       [-direction {in|out|all}]

       [-file <file_name>]

       [-level <level>]

       [-no_split]

       [-through_registers]

       [-to_ports]

       [-insts <inst+>] | [-ports <port+>] | [-selected]

       Reports the connections of specified macros, selected macros, or speci-
       fied ports. You can also report the input and output connectivity sepa-
       rately. By default it reports both.

Parameters
       -direction {in|out|all}
              Specifies the pin direction of objects to be reported.

              Default: all

              Data_type: string, optional

       -file <file_name>
              Specifies the name of the output report file in which the  trace
              macro results will be saved.

              Default: <top_module_name>.tmcrpt

              Data_type: string, optional

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each report_obj_connectivity parameter. For a  de-
              tailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use
              the man command: man report_obj_connectivity

       -insts <inst+>
              Specifies the macros to be reported.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -level <level>
              Specifies the trace level.

              Maximum: 10

              Minimum:  1

              Default: 5

              Data_type: int, optional

       -no_split
              Reports a single object per line.

       -ports <port+>
              Specifies the IO ports to be reported.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -through_registers
              Reports the through registers between selected objects.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -to_ports
              Reports the connectivity from the selected objects to IO ports.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -selected
              Reports the selected macros or IO ports.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Example
       The following command reports the selected macros or IO ports:

       report_obj_connectivity -selected

